@a.y.e.s.t.h.e.t.i.c.s why does the lgbtq+ get a month to celebrate their pride whereas people who gave their lives to our country get just a few days out of the year? Saying that you deserve all the recognition in the world and straights don’t is borderline hypocritical. I personally don’t care about having a pride month, because I don’t need to shove my sexuality down others throats to get attention. I have things to define me other than the gender I’m attracted to. The statistics show that straights are murdered far more than lgbtq, and even bullied just as frequently. We live in a modern world where these problems you would’ve faced just hardly exist anymore (except on rare occasions). In conclusion, saying you deserve recognition and others don’t is exactly what you’ve (apparently) been fighting against. It’s hypocrisy at best.
@coolaleco @coolaleco Hm, that’s funny because I’m a Muslim and I have no memory of ever doing that. How about you don’t judge 2 billion people by the actions of a few shitty governments?
@informed_love I never said that all Muslims did that

@ethanprestwood_64 honestly I agree with some of your statements despite being lgbt myself. Why pride month exists is to shed a bit of light on people who are oppressed in their every day lives. Hopefully with the progression of our society, pride month won't have to be something that exists anymore.
Wow someone got killed ladee fucking da
@coolaleco Imagine being this dumb
@coolaleco @coolaleco sweetheart, let’s not pretend that you weren’t being islamophobic as hell and generalizing and hating Muslims. Okay?
@informed_love I don't hate Muslims, I don't hate anybody, nice try though.
@coolaleco you’re extremely islamophobic and have proven it. Try again.
@informed_love you try again lol, just because I don't like someone's religion doesn't mean I hate them, nice try though 👍
@coolaleco islamophobia doesn’t mean outright hatred, sweetie. Your lack of education is really showing😬
@informed_love you said I hated Muslims, I said I didn't, your lack of basic understanding is really showing.
@coolaleco but the second time, I just said islamophobic (I’ll let you pretend you don’t hate Muslims) and you went on about how you don’t hate anyone

@coolaleco so let’s go through this step by step: 1. You were xenophobic and made the biased, unsubstantiated claim that refugees—people in need of our help—are the sole reason for the rise of anti-LGBTQ+ hate crimes (btw, most hate crimes are committed by white people) 2. I called you out on your xenophobia, and you randomly decided to be islamophobic as well 3. Then you fooled yourself and absolutely no one else into believing that you’re not a hateful ass bitch

@informed_love I don't care what you think about me honestly, I don't need you to pretend like you can understand what I'm saying because you clearly can't. Let me say it with smaller words this time. I can criticize (show the big bad things in something) and you can call me whatever you want for it. I know I don't hate anybody and that is that, I don't care if you think I am an islamaphobe because I disagree with sharia law.
@coolaleco Sharia Law isn’t Islam. You attacked Islam and Muslims. That’s islamophobic, dumbass
@informed_love you say I am the hateful one but you are calling me names.
@informed_love you are filled with so much hate... that is very hypocritical of you.

@coolaleco 1. Yeah, I think you as a person suck. That’s not the same as hating entire religions and their followers as well as immigrants who need help. 2. Not filled with hate. I just know that the world deserves better than you

@coolaleco Christianity has started countless wars and practically created oppression, but I’m still not hateful towards Christianity or its followers. At some point, you need to put aside your delusions and face your hatred.

@informed_love I don't hate anybody... You may think I hate you but I don't, there isn't a single person on earth I hate, because I follow the Bible and the true word of God. Everyone deserves to be in this world, you and me, whether you like it or not.
@coolaleco so you’re not putting aside your delusions of “haha I’m so loving unless I’m not!1!1!1!” Then?

@informed_love have you ever taken a history class? Islam is a major cause of war too! That's not why it's a bad religion, and Islam has created more oppression and division than Christianity lol, do you even know about Pakistan and India?
@coolaleco 1. I know Islam has started wars. Christianity has started more. 2. Nope. Christianity created most systems of oppression, often via colonization 3. Do you know anything at all?
Straight people who want a straight pride only want it cause they don't have any attention on them lol

I thought it was funny because the straight flag I think already exists but instead they made a new one that looks like a potential trans flag. The person who tried doing straight pride is also a white supremacist piece of human trash. Be careful if you’re straight and proud because you might accidentally rally w supremacist or Nazi garbage. Those are the kind of people that usually propose ridiculous things like a straight pride or a call for white rights.

@a.y.e.s.t.h.e.t.i.c.s fr though, I think it’s really cool y’all have a way to come together like this. To be clear, I’m by no means homophobic, at least not intentionally. I don’t hate any member of the lgbtq+, and honestly I could care less how you show your pride. I’m sure you’re a very nice, respectable person. The only people I don’t like are the radical lgbt members (the kind you see on YouTube videos) and I know this is a very inaccurate representation of who you, as a culture, are. I’m sure, like I said, as an individual, you and just about every other person identifying as lgbtq+ has a unique and interesting story to tell.

node.accessibility_caption: Image may contain: text that says '2 Straight cis people can travel without fear of being straight. Earlier this year, Brunei made headlines when they announced that they would punish homosexuality with death. When straight people are researching their holidays, are they also researching whether they'll be stoned to death on arrival?'

Image may contain: text that says '3. Straight cis people have always been able to legally marry. Same-sex marriage is still an ongoing battle in many parts of the world, and there's growing fear that in some places the new rights will be repealed. Imagine if the only cake-related drama at your wedding was the decision between gateau or sponge.'

Image may contain: text that says '4 Straight cis people have never been jailed for being straight. Being queer was criminalised until relatively recently, and while the actions of straight people are still punishable (unless they're exercising freedom of speech by being a bigot) they've never faced improsenment for who they love or how they identify.'

Image may contain: text that says '8 Straight cis people don't have to correct people on pronouns. Apart from the iconic 'They call me Mr. Pig! AAAAAAAH!!' scene in Lion King, straight cisgender people (or warthogs) don't often need to correct people on their preferred pronouns let alone go through months (if not years) of correspondence just to get a passport.'

Image may contain: text that says '9. Straight cis people aren't denied medical help for being straight. From the obvious procedures like gender confirmation surgery, and even down to emergency services, LGBTQ people still don't receive proper medical assistance on the basis of their identity. And don't even get us started on how we can't donate blood!'
